column117: The site is an active bush cemetery. Management of mowing to minimise impacts on the species - mowing to occur only after seed set, with thatch removal to reduce nutrient inputs. Some weed pulling. Efforts to begin fire regime to remove biomass are ongoing. Discussions to limit burial activity around orchid patches are ongoing. Seed collection occurs for wider conservation activities.

column5: Small Purple-pea, Mountain Swainson-pea, Small Purple Pea
column117: Population persists on an undeveloped suburban block. A secure rigid fence surrounds the plants to protect them from damage. Controlled burning occurs as required as there is no herbivory. Genetic rescue attempts are ongoing.

column5: Small Purple-pea, Mountain Swainson-pea, Small Purple Pea
column117: Population persists within a nature reserve. Rabbit and kangaroo control. Seed collection and orchard set up to provide plants for translocation in the future. Historical fire regime to promote recruitment (albeit unsuccessful).
